merican federation of labor Atlantic City, June 18, 1919 .... Buy war savings stamps. [1919].", "type": ["text"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2020782664/"}], "resource": {"fulltext_file": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/njr/batch_njr_jackson_ver01/data/sn92059905/00513685889/1924041601/0535.xml&format=alto_xml&full_text=1", "image": "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:njr:batch_njr_jackson_ver01:data:sn92059905:00513685889:1924041601:0492/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg", "pdf": "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/ndnp/njr/batch_njr_jackson_ver01/data/sn92059905/00513685889/1924041601/0535.pdf", "segment_count": 56, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn92059905/1924-04-16/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}, "resources": [{"fulltext_file": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/njr/batch_njr_jackson_ver01/data/sn92059905/00513685889/1924041601/0535.xml&format=alto_xml&full_text=1", "image": "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:njr:batch_njr_jackson_ver01:data:sn92059905:00513685889:1924041601:0492/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg", "pdf": "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/ndnp/njr/batch_njr_jackson_ver01/data/sn92059905/00513685889/1924041601/0535.pdf", "segment_count": 56, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn92059905/1924-04-16/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}], "segment_id": "/service/ndnp/njr/batch_njr_jackson_ver01/data/sn92059905/00513685889/1924041601/0535.xml", "segments": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn92059905/1924-04-16/ed-1/?sp=44"], "batch": ["njr_jackson_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "composite_location": ["0/united states/", "1/united states/new jersey/", "2/united states/new jersey/atlantic/", "3/united states/new jersey/atlantic/ventnor city/"], "contributor": ["rutgers university libraries"], "date": "1924-04-16", "dates": ["1924-04-16"], "description": ["STILL GOING STRONG THE GREAT HAT TRICK 1 W HE WAS FUNNY AT FIRSTS BUT HE MAKES ME NERVOUS Business Outlook Better Than Ever Declare Wm S Emley Former Head of Real Estate Board in Statement on Real Estate Conditions By H C Test From the standpoint of the man interested in real estate the outlook for business both in At lantic City and on Absecon Island was never better declared Wil liam S Emley former President of the Atlantic City Real Estate Board prominent civic leader and expert on real estate valuations in Atlantic City Ventnor and other neighbor resorts The en tire Island and its business is on such a solid foundation of values that there is nothing to stand in the way of constant growth and improvement It is my belief and the belief of most men who must use real vision in their business that we have merely scratched our market for those who should buy homes or enter business in Atlantic City Today we lie within a few hour ride of half the population of th United States and we have bui to call attention to our advantages as a resort and as a residence"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2025-12-01T12:42:00.300Z", "group": ["ndnp/njr", "rutgers-university-libraries-awardee"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn92059905/1924-04-16/ed-1/?sp=44", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:njr:batch_njr_jackson_ver01:data:sn92059905:00513685889:1924041601:0535/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=287&w=245", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:njr:batch_njr_jackson_ver01:data:sn92059905:00513685889:1924041601:0535/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=575&w=491", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:njr:batch_njr_jackson_ver01:data:sn92059905:00513685889:1924041601:0535/full/pct:25/0/default.jpg#h=1151&w=983", "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/ser